An alleged house burglar who was being interrogated by officials at Heidelberg Detective Branch on Ueckermann Street, southeast of Johannesburg, nearly escaped on Wednesday when he jumped from a second-floor window, Heidelberg/Nigel Heraut reports. Burglar treated The incident took place at about 12.10am and, according to eyewitnesses, the suspect only managed to run a few metres before the head and neck injuries he sustained from the fall proved to be too much to handle. READ MORE: Robber accidentally kills accomplice He collapsed in front of Standard Bank, where he received treatment from paramedics, who were quick to respond. He was later taken to Heidelberg Hospital. &#8211; Caxton News Service